# Installation
Femtoemacs is a SMALL clone of emacs,
that one can configure using FEMTOLISP.
It was designed by Hugh Barney. Here
is the femtoemacs page:

https://github.com/hughbarney/femto

Femtolisp was implemented by Jeff
Benzason, of Julia fame. Femtolisp page:

https://github.com/JeffBezanson/femtolisp

First install the ncurses library according
to instructions in libncursesw.readme

## Linux

make
sudo cp femto /usr/local/bin
sudo cp femto.boot /usr/local/bin
cp init.lsp ~/
cp aliases.scm ~/

## Mac OS-X

make -f Makefile.macosx
sudo cp femto /usr/local/bin
sudo cp femto.boot /usr/local/bin
cp init.lsp ~/
cp aliases.scm ~/

